    "recap_headline": "University of Delaware Athletics",
    "recap_text": "NEWARK, Del. -\nThe University of Delaware baseball program earned its first-ever Conference USA victory as the Fightin' Blue Hens defeated Dallas Baptist by a score of 5-4 on Friday at Bob Hannah Stadium.\nWith the win, Delaware's record improves to 10-12 overall (1-3 CUSA) while the Patriots fall to 12-10 (2-2 CUSA).\nHEN HIGHLIGHTS\nThe offense was engineered by three solo-home runs off the bats of\nEvan Bouldin\n,\nLT Cockrill\nand\nMatthew Minckler\n.\nFor Bouldin, it was his team-leading seventh home run of the season. Cockrill and Minckler both hit their second of the season.\nThe Blue Hens needed just two pitchers for Friday's win.\nRyan McLaughlin\nstarted on the mound and pitched a career-high five innings. He allowed four hits, two earned runs, and struck out two batters. He earned the win and is now 2-1.\nRyan Pugh\npitched a career-high four innings to close out the game. He also allowed four hits, two runs (one earned) and struck out five batters. He earned his first save of the season.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nBoudin kicked the game off with a solo-home run to left center field. The ball traveled 427 feet and had an exit velocity of 106 MPH.\nAfter DBU tied the game 1-1 in the top of the third, Cockrill hit a home run to deep left field to retake the lead.\nThe Blue Hens added onto their lead when\nAnthony DeCesare\ndrove in\nHarry Carr\noff an error in the fourth, and\nAnthony Charles\ngrounded into a double play to drive in Bouldin in the fifth.\nMinckler hit the go-head home run in the bottom of the sixth to left field to give the Blue Hens a 5-2 lead.\nDBU chipped away at the Delaware lead with an RBI double in the seventh and a home run in the eighth. But, Pugh shut the door on the Patriots comeback with a 1-2-3 ninth inning.\nGAME NOTES\nFourth year head coach\nGreg Mamula\nearned his 99th win as the Blue Hens skipper in Friday's win.\nUP NEXT\nGame two of the weekend series continues tomorrow at 2:05 p.m. Fans can watch the game on ESPN+.\nTICKETS\nSeason and individual tickets are available for all of Delaware's 2026 home games.\nClick here\nto secure your seats for the next game.\nFOLLOW ON SOCIAL\nFor the latest on Delaware baseball, follow the Blue Hens on\nX\n,\nInstagram\n, and like on\nFacebook\n.",
